      "chapterId": "chapter12",
      "type": "Term",
      "front": "Shakers",
      "back": "But the Shakers, the most successful of the religious communities, also had a significant impact on the outside world. The Shakers were founded in the late eighteenth century by Mother Ann Lee, the daughter of an English blacksmith, who became a religious exhorter and claimed that Christ had directed her to emigrate with her followers to America. God, the Shakers believed, had a \"dual\" personality, both male and female, and thus the two sexes were spiritually equal.",
      "hint": "But the Shakers, the most successful of the religious communities, also had a significant impact on the outside world.",
