      "chapterId": "chapter12",
      "type": "Term",
      "front": "New Harmony",
      "back": "Here, Owen established New Harmony, where he hoped to create a \"new moral world.\" \"The character of man is, without a single exception, always formed for him,\" Owen declared. At New Harmony, he promised, women would no longer be \"enslaved\" to their husbands, and \"false notions\" about innate differences between the sexes would be abandoned. Harmony eluded the residents of New Harmony.",
      "hint": "Here, Owen established New Harmony, where he hoped to create a \"new moral world.\" \"The character of man is, without a single exception, always formed for him,\" Owen declared.",
      "imageId": null,
